Bonang will no longer bring her fabulous personality to Metro FM, as she has resigned from the station.According to Daily Sun, she apparently handed in her resignation just an hour ago following her dissatisfaction with the station s decision to pair her with Lerato Kganyago as part of the new lineup.Bonang has since confirmed her departure, taking to Twitter to issue a short statement.After 3 years of making magic on the Front Row, I can confirm that I have officially stepped down as the host of the show&#8230;..&mdash; Bonang B* Matheba (@bonang_m) April 3, 2017I will miss my Metro FM family dearly, as they say all good things do come to an end&#8230;.Looking forward to the next chapter of my radio life&mdash; Bonang B* Matheba (@bonang_m) April 3, 2017Metro FM has announced several new changes to the station, with DJ Fresh presenting the breakfast show with Somizi.Metro FM also announced that Kganyago, commonly known as LKG , will be joining Bonang on her popular radio show, The Front Row, following Unathi Msengana and Glen Lewis s departure.Glen Lewis left to join Touch HD, former Metro DJ Tbo Touch s new online radio station. Unathi has yet to announce where she will be heading.